Root Cause
Access control enforced only at the reverse proxy.
Backend trusted client-controlled rewrite headers.
Missing authorization checks inside the application.
Impact
If exploited in a real application, an attacker may:

Access hidden administrator panels
Delete users
Modify administrator settings
View confidential information
Perform privileged administrative actions
This could result in a complete compromise of administrative functionality.

Prevention
Never trust user-controlled rewrite headers.
Remove X-Original-URL and X-Rewrite-URL before forwarding requests.
Enforce authorization checks in the backend application.
Never rely solely on reverse proxy URL filtering.
Validate permissions for every sensitive request.
